text: Nizhnelebyazhye () is a rural locality (a selo) in Raznochinovsky Selsoviet, Narimanovsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 225 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Volga River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Narimanovsky District
title: Nizhnelebyazhye
